The key insight is that the construction of the measure and the resolution of identity is such that when we integrate the identity function, we recover the original inner product. This is a standard result in the theory of self-adjoint operators, often related to the fact that the identity function corresponds to the identity operator in the functional calculus.

To prove this in Lean, we need to show that `inner ℂ x (a y) = (toComplexMeasure (toResolutionOfIdentity ha) x y).integral (Function.Embedding.subtype (spectrum ℂ a))`. This is a standard result in the theory of self-adjoint operators and their spectral measures. In Lean, this would involve showing that the integral of the identity function is the original inner product.

