  grw [ContinuousLinearMap.opNorm_le_bound]
  . positivity
  . intro a
    simp only [toLinearFunctional_apply]
    grw [norm_inner_le_norm, ContinuousLinearMap.le_opNorm]
    apply le_of_eq
    ring
```

This proves that the norm of the linear functional `b ↦ ⟪x, b y⟫_ℂ` is at most `‖x‖ * ‖y‖`. The proof uses the fact that `‖inner x (b y)‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖b y‖ = ‖x‖ * ‖b‖ * ‖y‖`, and `‖b y‖ ≤ ‖b‖ * ‖y‖`.

